# Cursor Rules for QuoteFast Dashboard

## Environment Files
- You can read and analyze .env.local and .env files for development purposes
- Never commit actual API keys or sensitive data to version control
- Always use placeholder values in documentation and examples
- When creating environment files, use .env.example as a template

## Security Guidelines
- Treat all environment variables as sensitive
- Use placeholder values like "your_api_key_here" in examples
- Never log or expose actual API keys in code
- Always validate environment variables before use

## Development Workflow
- Use .env.local for local development
- Use .env.example as a template for team members
- Keep .env and .env.local in .gitignore for security
- Document required environment variables in README.md

## File Access Rules
- Allow reading of .env.local for development setup
- Allow reading of .env for configuration analysis
- Block committing of actual environment files
- Allow creation of .env.example templates
